The official memorial service for the late Environmental Affairs Minister Edna Molewa will be held next Wednesday at the Tshwane Events Centre in Pretoria West. Molewa who passed away last Saturday at the age of 61 will be buried next weekend. She will be accorded an official funeral Category 1. The Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) on State Funerals, led by Minister in the Presidency Dr. Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma briefed the media in Pretoria on the latest regarding the funeral arrangements. “The official funeral service will be held on Saturday, 6 October 2018 from 08h00 in the morning at Tshwane Events Centre Hall J and proceed to Zandfontein Cemetery, Pretoria West. The funeral service will be open to members of the public. Mourners may attend evening prayer services which will be held at the Molewa residence daily at 19h00 until Friday, 5 October.” Meanwhile, Dlamini-Zuma says those who wish to send messages of condolences can make use of condolence books available at the following places. “At the Molewa family residence, the Union Buildings, Environmental Affair Departments in Pretoria and Cape Town, Premiers’ office in all provinces, Sefako Makgatho University.” Click below for more on the story: 